:markdown
  [WhereCampPDX](http://wherecamppdx.org) is Portland's yearly unconference at the intersection of geography, technology, design, and culture. [Audrey Eschright](http://lifeofaudrey.com) and I co-founded the event in 2008, drawing inspiration from earlier WhereCamps held in the bay area.

  I designed WhereCampPDX's northwest compass logo and other conference materials in 2008 and have   updated the WhereCampPDX website using a new map of Portland each year.

